# geom-core Build Configuration
#
# This is a C++ geometry library with Python and WebAssembly bindings.
# It has no runtime service environment variables. These variables control
# the build process only.
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Adjust build settings as needed
# 3. Never commit .env file to version control

# ============================================
# CMake Build Configuration
# ============================================

# Build type: Release | Debug | RelWithDebInfo | MinSizeRel
CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release

# ============================================
# Optional: OCCT (Open CASCADE) for STEP Support
# ============================================

# Set to ON to enable STEP/STP file loading (requires OCCT installed)
# Ubuntu: sudo apt-get install libocct-data-exchange-dev libocct-ocaf-dev
# macOS:  brew install opencascade
# USE_OCCT=OFF

# If OCCT is installed in a non-standard location:
# OCCT_WASM_ROOT=/path/to/occt-wasm

# ============================================
# Optional: Emscripten (for WebAssembly builds)
# ============================================

# Source the Emscripten SDK before building WASM:
#   source ~/emsdk/emsdk_env.sh
# EMSDK=/path/to/emsdk

# ============================================
# Quick Start
# ============================================
#
# Python bindings:
#   ./scripts/build_python.sh
#   # or: pip install -e .
#
# WebAssembly bindings:
#   source ~/emsdk/emsdk_env.sh
#   ./scripts/build_wasm.sh
#
# Run tests:
#   ./scripts/run_tests.sh
#   pytest tests/
#
# TypeScript package:
#   pnpm install && pnpm build
